1002
01:00:51.041 --> 01:00:53.208
We were like two little mad scientists.

1003
01:00:54.875 --> 01:00:57.874
We always thought we were
on the verge of discovering something

1004
01:00:57.875 --> 01:00:59.500
the world had never seen.

1005
01:01:02.916 --> 01:01:05.625
<i>Either way I lose.</i>

1006
01:01:09.750 --> 01:01:11.750
<i>Though I know…</i>

1007
01:01:13.458 --> 01:01:14.625
My sister…

1008
01:01:15.583 --> 01:01:16.916
Isabelle. she died.

1009
01:01:17.791 --> 01:01:20.875
In November. She had cystic fibrosis.

1010
01:01:22.458 --> 01:01:23.749
I'm so sorry. Jill.

1011
01:01:23.750 --> 01:01:26.125
She was just the love of my life. No big.

1012
01:01:27.541 --> 01:01:29.875
- I bet she's proud of you.
- Uh…

1013
01:01:32.125 --> 01:01:36.166
I was much cooler as a kid. I peaked at like 12.

1014
01:01:37.916 --> 01:01:41.749
I would do the craziest shit
just to come home with a story for her.

1015
01:01:41.750 --> 01:01:43.510
I would've tried crack if it made her laugh.

1016
01:01:44.041 --> 01:01:48.249
And now. I think I might be a little bit dead inside.

1017
01:01:48.250 --> 01:01:49.250
Jill…

1018
01:01:52.833 --> 01:01:54.958
You couldn't be less dead inside.

1019
01:01:56.666 --> 01:01:57.915
What you need to do

1020
01:01:57.916 --> 01:01:59.708
is you need to get out there

1021
01:02:00.291 --> 01:02:01.291
and try crack.

1022
01:02:04.291 --> 01:02:05.291
Come with me…

1023
01:02:07.166 --> 01:02:08.708
To Breeda and Andy's wedding.

1024
01:02:10.000 --> 01:02:11.000
Hm.

1025
01:02:12.541 --> 01:02:14.208
Okay.

1026
01:02:14.833 --> 01:02:16.666
I'll ask my overlord.

1027
01:02:19.416 --> 01:02:20.416
All right.

1028
01:02:21.791 --> 01:02:23.082
Ready for the main course?

1029
01:02:23.083 --> 01:02:24.166
There's more?

1030
01:02:25.541 --> 01:02:28.415
- I… This was already so impressive.
- Come on!

1031
01:02:28.416 --> 01:02:30.374
How could you make more? I don't even…

1032
01:02:30.375 --> 01:02:31.875
- Shut up.
- You can't top this.

1033
01:02:35.083 --> 01:02:36.083
Okay.

1034
01:02:39.625 --> 01:02:42.833
<i>Either way I lose…</i>

1035
01:02:44.291 --> 01:02:45.915
Is that chicken pot pie?

1036
01:02:45.916 --> 01:02:47.708
With cornbread crust.

1037
01:02:49.750 --> 01:02:51.082
You made this for me?

1038
01:02:51.083 --> 01:02:53.832
Yeah. I mean. I have no idea
if it's anything like your mom's.

1039
01:02:53.833 --> 01:02:56.916
It was a full-blown experiment. but we will see.

1040
01:02:57.583 --> 01:02:58.583
All right.

1041
01:03:25.291 --> 01:03:26.583
Uh…

1042
01:03:28.250 --> 01:03:32.291
I'm gonna go… Just… I'm gonna prep dessert. okay?

1043
01:03:58.541 --> 01:04:00.874
<i>Believe it</i>

1044
01:04:00.875 --> 01:04:05.041
<i>I need you by my side.</i>

1045
01:04:05.541 --> 01:04:07.957
<i>Yes. I know you know.</i>

1046
01:04:07.958 --> 01:04:12.332
<i>Know you know Know I've been a sinner. baby</i>

1047
01:04:12.333 --> 01:04:14.707
<i>I've seen it</i>

1048
01:04:14.708 --> 01:04:18.791
<i>I've seen you high and dry.</i>

1049
01:04:19.708 --> 01:04:21.874
<i>Yes. I know you don't.</i>

1050
01:04:21.875 --> 01:04:27.832
<i>Know you don't Know you don't need me to say it.</i>

1051
01:04:27.833 --> 01:04:30.958
<i>But if anything happens between us Does everything change?</i>

1052
01:04:32.333 --> 01:04:37.290
<i>I know you feel it too I can see it in your face.</i>

1053
01:04:37.291 --> 01:04:41.458
<i>So tell me now not to get too close</i>

1054
01:04:42.750 --> 01:04:44.040
<i>'Cause it always happens.</i>

1055
01:04:44.041 --> 01:04:46.624
<i>One. two. three. four.</i>

1056
01:04:46.625 --> 01:04:49.374
<i>How much longer can this go?</i>

1057
01:04:49.375 --> 01:04:51.207
<i>Oh. babe. don't break.</i>

1058
01:04:51.208 --> 01:04:53.874
<i>Every single breath you take.</i>

1059
01:04:53.875 --> 01:04:58.040
<i>Kills me softly. chills my body.</i>

1060
01:04:58.041 --> 01:04:59.833
<i>But when we reach the limit.</i>

1061
01:05:01.458 --> 01:05:02.499
- Sorry.
- No. Sorry.

1062
01:05:02.500 --> 01:05:04.460
- Yeah… I just have to go to the bathroom.
- Okay.

1063
01:05:05.333 --> 01:05:06.332
All right. You okay?

1064
01:05:06.333 --> 01:05:07.249
- Yep.
- Okay.

1065
01:05:07.250 --> 01:05:08.708
- Sorry. Uh…
- Oh. no. Okay.

1066
01:05:10.750 --> 01:05:11.750
Okay.

1067
01:05:13.916 --> 01:05:15.915
Just say it. Just say the words.

1068
01:05:15.916 --> 01:05:17.374
Just say it.

1069
01:05:17.375 --> 01:05:19.541
Jill. Hey. Jill. I've been…

1070
01:05:20.416 --> 01:05:23.000
I've been getting your voice mails. I've been getting…

1071
01:05:25.208 --> 01:05:27.750
Oh. shit.

1072
01:05:46.333 --> 01:05:47.333
Jill.

1073
01:05:48.750 --> 01:05:49.791
Uh…

1074
01:05:52.916 --> 01:05:54.125
I. um…

1075
01:05:58.958 --> 01:06:00.000
No. it's okay.

1076
01:06:01.041 --> 01:06:02.250
It's totally okay.

1077
01:06:03.500 --> 01:06:04.500
Um…

1078
01:06:06.333 --> 01:06:08.041
Want to just watch <i>Top Chef</i>?

1079
01:06:08.833 --> 01:06:12.790
<i>I took a date-based ganache.
I shaped it into a small sphere.</i>

1080
01:06:12.791 --> 01:06:15.915
<i>and I coated it in a cocoa-infused beignet dough before…</i>

1081
01:06:15.916 --> 01:06:18.083
Jill. I've been getting your voice mails.

1082
01:06:18.625 --> 01:06:20.957
<i>I like the surprise in the middle. It's nice.</i>

1083
01:06:20.958 --> 01:06:23.582
<i>I went with a bombolone-style donut.</i>

1084
01:06:23.583 --> 01:06:26.749
<i>I worked in fresh orange and lemon zest. fried it off.</i>

1085
01:06:26.750 --> 01:06:29.582
<i>and finished it with a passion fruit cream filling.</i>

1086
01:06:29.583 --> 01:06:31.249
<i>The texture's great.</i>

1087
01:06:31.250 --> 01:06:32.832
<i>Heaven help me.</i>

1088
01:06:32.833 --> 01:06:38.000
<i>My mind changes like the wind.</i>

1089
01:06:40.041 --> 01:06:42.332
<i>Please excuse me</i>

1090
01:06:42.333 --> 01:06:47.832
<i>I don't know where to begin.</i>

1091
01:06:47.833 --> 01:06:51.749
<i>But I didn't think I cared</i>

1092
01:06:51.750 --> 01:06:54.124
<i>I could be your friend.</i>

1093
01:06:54.125 --> 01:06:58.832
<i>But I'm unprepared Oh. I've never felt like this</i>

1094
01:06:58.833 --> 01:07:01.124
<i>I was unaware.</i>

1095
01:07:01.125 --> 01:07:03.582
<i>That you were lighting flares.</i>

1096
01:07:03.583 --> 01:07:08.457
<i>Now I'm running scared Oh. how did it come to this?</i>

1097
01:07:08.458 --> 01:07:15.458
<i>You know I've never Been so lonely on my own.</i>

1098
01:07:16.041 --> 01:07:17.999
<i>And it shows</i>

1099
01:07:18.000 --> 01:07:22.791
<i>'Cause I don't see you like I used to.</i>

1100
01:07:23.958 --> 01:07:26.582
<i>Now I'm going back On the things that I know.</i>

1101
01:07:26.583 --> 01:07:32.832
<i>Oh. all my nights taste like gold.</i>

1102
01:07:32.833 --> 01:07:37.082
<i>Yeah. when I'm with you It's like everything glows.</i>

1103
01:07:37.083 --> 01:07:42.165
<i>And all my days. we can lay low.</i>

1104
01:07:42.166 --> 01:07:46.625
<i>Yeah. when we're waking up We're waking up slow.</i>

1105
01:07:51.083 --> 01:07:52.791
Dessert tacos.

1106
01:07:53.625 --> 01:07:54.875
Dessert tacos?

1107
01:07:55.375 --> 01:07:58.249
When Izzy was super sick. they tried to get her to eat.

1108
01:07:58.250 --> 01:08:00.666
and she'd throw everything up except her favorite.

1109
01:08:01.583 --> 01:08:06.500
Dessert tacos. And <i>that</i> is my specialty.

1110
01:08:12.666 --> 01:08:13.958
<i>Magic: The Gathering.</i>

1111
01:08:14.666 --> 01:08:15.833
The card game?

1112
01:08:17.666 --> 01:08:20.207
Actually. they're not just cards.
They're actually collectible.

1113
01:08:20.208 --> 01:08:21.665
They're really valuable.

1114
01:08:21.666 --> 01:08:24.250
But. um. my mom. uh…

1115
01:08:24.916 --> 01:08:26.957
She would buy them for me.

1116
01:08:26.958 --> 01:08:29.708
and she bought me my first pack. and…

1117
01:08:30.791 --> 01:08:34.665
I just need the Alpha Black Lotus
to complete the Power Nine.

1118
01:08:34.666 --> 01:08:37.290
It's one of the rarest cards in the world.

1119
01:08:37.291 --> 01:08:40.082
That's what I've been… working towards.

1120
01:08:40.083 --> 01:08:41.082
Wow.

1121
01:08:41.083 --> 01:08:44.582
And I think I may have found one on eBay.

1122
01:08:44.583 --> 01:08:45.915
- Really?
- Yeah.

1123
01:08:45.916 --> 01:08:46.916
So…

1124
01:08:47.500 --> 01:08:50.957
I gotta confess. I was actually gonna ghost you

1125
01:08:50.958 --> 01:08:54.332
for not having the full… Power Nine.

1126
01:08:54.333 --> 01:08:55.790
So now I don't have to.

1127
01:08:55.791 --> 01:08:57.290
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1128
01:08:57.291 --> 01:08:59.791
Okay. wow. Still in the game.

1129
01:09:01.000 --> 01:09:02.250
Still in the game.

1130
01:09:03.875 --> 01:09:05.082
I'll see you at home.

1131
01:09:05.083 --> 01:09:06.083
Yeah.

1132
01:09:06.500 --> 01:09:07.541
Safe flight.

1133
01:09:08.458 --> 01:09:09.458
Thanks.

1134
01:09:30.375 --> 01:09:32.749
Last breath of freedom till you're chained for life.

1135
01:09:32.750 --> 01:09:34.666
- Hey!
- Yay!

1136
01:09:36.583 --> 01:09:38.624
Oh! We are excited to meet Jill.

1137
01:09:38.625 --> 01:09:40.250
Yeah. we are.

1138
01:09:41.750 --> 01:09:43.165
Oh. no.

1139
01:09:43.166 --> 01:09:44.165
I knew it.

1140
01:09:44.166 --> 01:09:45.332
What happened. Wes?

1141
01:09:45.333 --> 01:09:47.083
Nothing. Nothing.

1142
01:09:47.791 --> 01:09:49.874
We're just hanging out.

1143
01:09:49.875 --> 01:09:54.415
All right. I admit that things
have gotten a little intense.

1144
01:09:54.416 --> 01:09:58.540
Intense? You're the one
that flew to another city for this girl.

1145
01:09:58.541 --> 01:10:00.790
No. I flew to another city for work.

1146
01:10:00.791 --> 01:10:03.124
- Oh. for work.
- Oh. yes. of course.

1147
01:10:03.125 --> 01:10:04.665
- It was a work trip.
- Work trip. and...

1148
01:10:04.666 --> 01:10:07.165
All I'm saying is once in a while. Wes.

1149
01:10:07.166 --> 01:10:10.665
someone comes along that changes the whole game.

1150
01:10:10.666 --> 01:10:13.916
Yeah. don't be so busy scoring that you miss it.

1151
01:10:15.083 --> 01:10:16.874
Wow.

1152
01:10:16.875 --> 01:10:19.332
- That was good. So good.
- That was nice.

1153
01:10:19.333 --> 01:10:21.582
- Copyright that.
- Every single time.

1154
01:10:21.583 --> 01:10:25.458
Wait a minute. Wait. You didn't tell us
what happened with the voice mails.

1155
01:10:27.875 --> 01:10:29.749
- You didn't tell her?
- O.M. God.

1156
01:10:29.750 --> 01:10:30.665
I'm going to.

1157
01:10:30.666 --> 01:10:32.040
- Liar. liar!
- Guys. look.

1158
01:10:32.041 --> 01:10:35.540
Oh. my God. this is like a sick reboot of <i>You've Got Mail</i>.

1159
01:10:35.541 --> 01:10:37.457
Tom Hanks is America's sweetheart!

1160
01:10:37.458 --> 01:10:39.541
You are not Tom Hanks!

1161
01:10:40.041 --> 01:10:41.249
I might slap him.

1162
01:10:41.250 --> 01:10:42.915
- Violence is never...
- Slap him.

1163
01:10:42.916 --> 01:10:45.582
- Hey! Hey!
- Wes. tell her the truth.

1164
01:10:45.583 --> 01:10:47.540
- I'm going to.
- Okay? Yes.

1165
01:10:47.541 --> 01:10:51.540
- Tell her the truth. Wes.
- I will! In person.

1166
01:10:51.541 --> 01:10:52.958
I swear on my mom.

1167
01:10:56.708 --> 01:10:59.000
- Well. now we can't say anything.
- Yeah.

1168
01:11:18.000 --> 01:11:21.207
<i>I don't wanna see you smile</i>

1169
01:11:21.208 --> 01:11:24.124
<i>I want you in the morning.</i>

1170
01:11:24.125 --> 01:11:27.375
<i>Before you go performing.</i>

1171
01:11:29.500 --> 01:11:32.874
<i>Tell me something I don't know.</i>

1172
01:11:32.875 --> 01:11:38.583
<i>And lead me to the place Where no one ever goes.</i>

1173
01:11:40.791 --> 01:11:43.790
<i>You know you're beautiful.</i>

1174
01:11:43.791 --> 01:11:46.457
<i>But that ain't half the gold treasure In your soul.</i>

1175
01:11:46.458 --> 01:11:49.374
<i>What you got? 'Cause I want it all.</i>

1176
01:11:49.375 --> 01:11:51.957
<i>With your fingers in my mouth I fail to see your faults.</i>

1177
01:11:51.958 --> 01:11:59.665
<i>So please don't let me fall.</i>

1178
01:11:59.666 --> 01:12:11.583
<i>Don't let me fall.</i>

1179
01:12:13.291 --> 01:12:15.291
Good evening. everyone. I'm Wes.

1180
01:12:18.958 --> 01:12:21.665
Andy's younger. dreamier cousin.

1181
01:12:21.666 --> 01:12:23.207
- Lies.
- If not by blood.

1182
01:12:23.208 --> 01:12:24.875
Our mothers were best friends.

1183
01:12:25.708 --> 01:12:28.790
And Breeda is the older sister that I never had.

1184
01:12:28.791 --> 01:12:30.040
Aww.

1185
01:12:30.041 --> 01:12:35.124
So I tried to warn 'em both
that marriage is Russian roulette. okay?

1186
01:12:35.125 --> 01:12:38.041
- Should we go over the divorce rate?
- No.

1187
01:12:38.791 --> 01:12:43.749
Okay. suffice it to say.
I wouldn't consider myself a romantic.

1188
01:12:43.750 --> 01:12:44.791
Aw.

1189
01:12:50.333 --> 01:12:51.708
But. um…

1190
01:12:53.208 --> 01:12:57.874
Did you know that these two weren't even supposed to meet?

1191
01:12:57.875 --> 01:13:00.207
Andy's alarm randomly didn't go off.

1192
01:13:00.208 --> 01:13:04.165
This man has never been late
to anything in his entire life.

1193
01:13:04.166 --> 01:13:07.416
And he missed his dentist appointment.
And he loves the dentist.

1194
01:13:09.166 --> 01:13:10.082
- It's true.
- I do.

1195
01:13:10.083 --> 01:13:13.833
They made him wait for an hour.
and he was about to walk out.

1196
01:13:14.583 --> 01:13:15.957
when Breeda walked in.

1197
01:13:15.958 --> 01:13:17.165
Aww.

1198
01:13:17.166 --> 01:13:19.833
If that alarm had gone off when it was supposed to.

1199
01:13:20.791 --> 01:13:24.041
these two would never have met.
and we would not be here tonight.

1200
01:13:26.166 --> 01:13:28.541
I don't know about gambling on forever.

1201
01:13:30.208 --> 01:13:31.583
but I do know this.

1202
01:13:32.083 --> 01:13:33.791
You're proof

1203
01:13:34.583 --> 01:13:36.250
that sometimes

1204
01:13:37.916 --> 01:13:39.875
life rigs things in our favor.

1205
01:13:47.666 --> 01:13:48.790
To Breeda and Andy.

1206
01:13:48.791 --> 01:13:50.416
Yeah!

1207
01:13:53.041 --> 01:13:54.416
You made a believer out of me.

1208
01:13:59.166 --> 01:14:02.999
- I am so proud of you.
- Couldn't have done it without you. coach.

1209
01:14:03.000 --> 01:14:04.290
That was beautiful.

1210
01:14:04.291 --> 01:14:06.457
- Your hands are so cold.
- I know.

1211
01:14:06.458 --> 01:14:08.665
What?

1212
01:14:08.666 --> 01:14:10.124
Wait. let's warm you up.

1213
01:14:10.125 --> 01:14:11.125
Jeez.

1214
01:14:14.000 --> 01:14:15.000
Thanks.

1215
01:14:15.458 --> 01:14:17.583
- Can I top you off?
- Yes. please.

1216
01:14:19.166 --> 01:14:20.166
Thanks.

1217
01:14:21.958 --> 01:14:23.665
- There she is.
- Oh. my God! Jill!

1218
01:14:23.666 --> 01:14:25.540
Oh. wow. I am so starstruck.

1219
01:14:25.541 --> 01:14:27.207
Oh. my God!

1220
01:14:27.208 --> 01:14:29.915
<i>We can ride the storm…</i>

1221
01:14:29.916 --> 01:14:32.707
Can I get one more and a whiskey on the rocks?

1222
01:14:32.708 --> 01:14:35.165
- Yes.
- Thank you for being here. You're so cute.

1223
01:14:35.166 --> 01:14:37.416
- Congrats!
- Enjoy. Thank you!

1224
01:14:39.041 --> 01:14:41.375
- Oh. my God.
- Look who decided to show up!

1225
01:14:46.875 --> 01:14:52.375
<i>We can make it through it all.</i>

1226
01:14:53.541 --> 01:14:57.375
<i>Go and show us what we really are.</i>

1227
01:15:13.250 --> 01:15:15.540
- Oh. my God. are you okay?
- I'm so sorry.

1228
01:15:15.541 --> 01:15:16.958
- Are you all right?
- Sorry.

1229
01:15:17.791 --> 01:15:20.082
Jill! Hey. Jill! Jill. wait!

1230
01:15:20.083 --> 01:15:23.041
Why is my sister's number connected to your phone. Wes?

1231
01:15:24.166 --> 01:15:26.415
Okay. it's... It's a crazy story.

1232
01:15:26.416 --> 01:15:28.374
I… I got a work phone.

1233
01:15:28.375 --> 01:15:30.957
and then I inherited your sister's phone number.

1234
01:15:30.958 --> 01:15:33.291
- What are you talking about? How?
- After she died.

1235
01:15:34.208 --> 01:15:36.000
But my sister died in November.

1236
01:15:41.708 --> 01:15:43.791
So. you've been getting my…

1237
01:15:45.541 --> 01:15:47.583
Voicemails this entire time?

1238
01:15:48.083 --> 01:15:52.457
I was going to tell you. I just… Things kept happening.

1239
01:15:52.458 --> 01:15:53.791
- And I...
- What did you hear?

1240
01:15:56.708 --> 01:15:58.125
Wes. what did you hear?

1241
01:16:04.708 --> 01:16:05.916
My bench?

1242
01:16:06.458 --> 01:16:08.832
You knew that I was gonna be at my bench.

1243
01:16:08.833 --> 01:16:11.082
You knew about José's. about my fantasy.

1244
01:16:11.083 --> 01:16:13.375
You knew about my sister. You knew everything?

1245
